26/07/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Military commandos arrested on Friday (July 24th) five Somali pirates in the Gulf of Aden off the Somali coast.
The pirates were detained in an operation that involved the Gediz frigate as well as Turkish military special units operating as part of a NATO patrol.
Currently, two Turkish vessels are involved involved in anti-pirate operations off Somalia.
(AP, Reuters, Xinhua - 24/07/09)
